            <h1>ONA Area Directors</h1>
            <p>Area Directors and the Club Services Chair are appointed by the elected ONA executive and
are the eyes and ears of the Local Clubs.</p>
        </header>

        <p>
        Area Directors are responsible for reporting issues and
        activities back to the ONA Club Services Chair and ONA executive. Area Directors also form
        part of the ONA executive. At the same time, they should keep the Local Clubs informed of
        any changing conditions with regards to the hobby including any regulatory concerns. Area
        Directors are required to attend each of their responsible Club meetings a minimum of Once
        per year. Activity reports are usually sent to the Club Services Director who will summarize
        Local Club events in the Ontario Numismatist Newsletter, issued once every two months.
        </p>

